<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-08-12T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-08-12T17:00:00-05:00" n="427" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d427">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.796/8–246: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Pawley</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-08-12T18:00:00-04:00">August 12, 1946—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1081. <gloss target="#t_CAA1">CAA</gloss> unenthusiastic over Brazilian
                            proposed technical assistance agreement but will probably await Tippett
                            arrival before recommending changes to Dept. Dept. suggests advisability
                            at <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> discretion <pb facs="0495" n="477" xml:id="pg_477"/> of deferring conclusion civil aviation
                            technical assistance pending outcome bilateral transport
                            negotiations.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>